@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{doom-modeline-extras.el} extends the @samp{doom-modeline} package with
custom modeline segments, a dedicated modeline layout for Claude Code
sessions, and enhanced handling of GitHub notifications.

The package defines several modeline segments that surface contextual
information not provided by the standard @samp{doom-modeline} segments:

@itemize
@item
A @strong{Claude Code status} segment that displays the session name, model,
token count, cost, context usage percentage, lines changed, duration,
and cache efficiency for active Claude Code sessions.
@item
An @strong{AI context} segment showing how many files are currently in the
@samp{gptel} context.
@item
An @strong{Org Roam backlinks} segment displaying the backlink count for the
current node.
@item
A @strong{Tlon split mode} segment indicating when @code{tlon-split-mode} is active.
@item
A @strong{Tlon paragraph} segment showing paragraph-level information from
@code{tlon-paragraphs-mode-line-mode}.
@end itemize

On the notifications side, the package hooks into Doom Modeline's GitHub
notification fetching to automatically pull Forge notifications when new
GitHub notifications arrive.

