@node Claude Code status
@section Claude Code status

@findex doom-modeline-extras--format-claude-status
The @code{claude-code-status} segment is the most feature-rich segment in
this package.  It activates only in buffers recognized as Claude Code
sessions (via @code{claude-code--buffer-p}).  When session status data is
available, it displays multiple pipe-separated fields:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Backend icon}: the registered backend's icon, rendered via
@code{agent-backend-icon-string} from the @samp{agent} package.
@item
@strong{Session name}: shown in bold, extracted from the buffer name.
@item
@strong{Model}: the Claude model in use (e.g., ``opus'', ``sonnet'').
@item
@strong{Effort}: the Claude Code reasoning effort level (e.g., ``high'').
@item
@strong{Account}: the Claude account used for this session (e.g., ``personal'',
``work''), when multi-account support is configured.
@item
@strong{Rate limit burn rate}: shown as @samp{5h:+N% 7d:-M%} when
@code{doom-modeline-extras-claude-code-usage} is non-@code{nil}.  Each figure
is a deviation from the expected usage at this point in the window,
assuming uniform consumption across the entire period.  A positive
value (red) means the user is burning through the budget faster than
sustainable; a negative value (green) means the user is under budget.
Hovering shows a tooltip with raw utilization and the relative reset
time (e.g., ``27% used, -66% vs pace / Resets: in 2h 30m'').  The
underlying data comes from the usage polling in @samp{agent-claude}
(@ref{Top,agent-claude,,agent-claude,}).
@item
@strong{Token count}: formatted compactly (e.g., ``12.3k'', ``1.5M'').
@item
@strong{Cost}: shown as a dollar amount, optionally with strikethrough on
subscription plans (@ref{Claude Code cost display}).
@item
@strong{Context usage}: shown as a percentage with color coding---green below
60%, yellow at 60-79%, red at 80% and above.
@item
@strong{Lines changed}: a +N/-M display with green for additions and red for
deletions.
@item
@strong{Duration}: elapsed session time in a compact format (e.g., ``5m23s'').
@item
@strong{Cache efficiency}: the ratio of cache-read tokens to total tokens,
color-coded (green above 80%, yellow 50-79%, red below 50%).
@item
@strong{Alert indicator}: from @code{agent-alert-indicator}.
@end itemize

Codex sessions display the session name, configured model, reasoning
effort, account, elapsed duration, and alert indicator when those values
are available.  The reasoning effort comes from the live Codex buffer
override first, falling back to the account's @samp{config.toml}.

Before Claude status data arrives, the segment displays only the session
name.

The formatting is handled by several internal helper functions:
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-model},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-account},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-effort},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-tokens},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-cost},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-context-percent},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-lines-changed},
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-duration}, and
@code{doom-modeline-extras--format-cache-efficiency}.

@node Tlon segments
@section Tlon segments

The @code{tlon-split} segment displays the literal string ``split'' when
@code{tlon-split-mode} is active and @code{doom-modeline-extras-tlon-split} is
non-@code{nil}.

The @code{tlon-paragraph} segment displays paragraph information from
@code{tlon-paragraphs-mode-line-string} when @code{tlon-paragraphs-mode-line-mode}
is active.

@node Org Roam backlinks
@section Org Roam backlinks

The @code{org-roam-backlinks} segment displays the backlink count for the
current Org Roam node.  It reads the buffer-local variable
@code{org-roam-extras-current-backlink-count} (managed by
@samp{org-roam-extras.el}) and formats the count as a recycling symbol with a
count in parentheses.  The segment appears only in @code{org-mode} buffers
when @code{doom-modeline-extras-org-roam} is non-@code{nil}.

@node AI context
@section AI context

The @code{ai-context} segment displays the number of files currently in the
@samp{gptel} AI context list (@code{gptel-context--alist}).  It appears only when
@code{doom-modeline-extras-ai-context} is non-@code{nil} and the context is
non-empty.

@node Modeline definitions
@chapter Modeline definitions

The package defines a @code{claude-code} modeline layout using
@code{doom-modeline-def-modeline}.  This layout places the @code{claude-code-status}
segment on the left side (alongside the bar segment) and @code{misc-info},
@code{major-mode}, @code{process}, and @code{time} on the right.  It is intended for
use in Claude Code session buffers to give a comprehensive at-a-glance
view of the session state.

