@node GitHub notification handling
@section GitHub notification handling

@findex doom-modeline-extras-handle-github-notifications
@findex doom-modeline-extras-refresh-github-after-forge
@vindex doom-modeline-extras-github-last-count
The function @code{doom-modeline-extras-handle-github-notifications} is
added to @code{doom-modeline-after-github-fetch-notification-hook}.  After
Doom Modeline fetches the GitHub notification count, this function
compares the new count against the previously stored count in the
variable @code{doom-modeline-extras-github-last-count}.

When the count has changed and is greater than zero, the function calls
@code{forge-extras-pull-notifications} from the @samp{forge-extras} package to
retrieve full notification details.  It then updates the stored count.
This provides a bridge between Doom Modeline's lightweight notification
polling and Forge's detailed notification management.

The function @code{doom-modeline-extras-refresh-github-after-forge} works in
the opposite direction: it is installed as @samp{:after} advice on
@code{forge--ghub-update-notifications} so that after Forge pulls
notifications, the Doom Modeline GitHub count updates immediately
rather than waiting for the next timer cycle.

@node Formatting helpers
@section Formatting helpers

@findex doom-modeline-extras--humanize-tokens
@findex doom-modeline-extras--humanize-duration
@findex doom-modeline-extras--context-face
@findex doom-modeline-extras--cache-face
The function @code{doom-modeline-extras--humanize-tokens} formats a token
count into a compact string using ``k'' and ``M'' suffixes.  For example,
1500 becomes ``1.5k'' and 2000000 becomes ``2.0M''.

The function @code{doom-modeline-extras--humanize-duration} formats
milliseconds into a compact time string.  For example, 125000 becomes
``2m5s'' and 7200000 becomes ``2h0m''.

The function @code{doom-modeline-extras--context-face} returns a face based
on context usage percentage: @code{doom-modeline-info} below 60%,
@code{doom-modeline-warning} between 60% and 79%, and @code{doom-modeline-urgent}
at 80% or above.

The function @code{doom-modeline-extras--cache-face} returns a face based on
cache hit percentage, using the inverse scale: @code{doom-modeline-info} at
80% or above, @code{doom-modeline-warning} between 50% and 79%, and
@code{doom-modeline-urgent} below 50%.

